commitResults.messageTitle: Modify Find Command to allow for finding by field
commitResults.messageBody:
Instead of searching only by role, users now include a specifier to
indicate which field they want to search by.
Update javadocs for Delete Command
Add Deadline Command to ApplicationBook
Reorder role and company in EditCommand

* Reordered `role` and `company` in test class.
* Changed `isValidSpecifier` to return a boolean.
* Updated tests for `isValidSpecifier` accordingly.
* Updated error message for invalid specifier.
Update the UG to reflect usage of the `find` command.
Add test case to check that invalid specifiers are handled correctly.

* Replaced `"d/"` with `PREFIX_DEADLINE`.
* Renamed test by replacing `Person` with `Job`.

* Changed `Company.name` regex to accept symbols.
* Changed relevant tests in CommandTestUtil, CompanyTest and
JsonAdaptedJobTest

* Reordered `COMPANY` to be before `ROLE` in `AddCommand` usage.
* `DeleteCommand`: Changed "person" to "job" in comment and successful
deletion string.
* Changed `Company` to be the main field after adding a new `Job`.
Change implementation of edit and add deadline

* `unsortJobs()` method added to all 3 classes.
* `UniqueJobList` now contains a `unsortedInternalList` list which
stores the original unsorted list of jobs.
Update EditCommand to allow editing of status

* The `list` command can now take in a specifier which indicates which
field to sort the list by.
* When the `list` command is called without a specifier, the system
preserves the current sorting.
* Tests have not been updated.
* List by status has not been implemented.

Changed the descriptions for the `find` and `sort` commands to reflect
the latest functionality.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update `list` and `sort` commands in the DG
commitResults.messageBody:
Added an overview and implementation description for the above commands
in the developer guide.

UML diagrams and design considerations have yet to be added.

* `list` now removes and filter but preserves sort order.
* `find` now supports searching by multiple fields. All keywords
provided must match.
* `find` and `sort` commands can be done on all fields.

Tests are not implemented yet.

Prefixes are now used instead of specifiers for the `sort` command.
This reduces confusion in users regarding the differences between a specifier and a prefix.

* Tests added for `CombinedPredicate` and `FindCommandParser`.
* Fixed `FindCommandParser` to throw an exception when a preamble is
present in the command.

Other changes:
* Changed user messages displayed by `FindCommandParser`, `SortCommand` and `Status`.
* Updated UG structure.

* `find` command now supports searching without a prefix.
* If multiple keywords are provided in the preamble, all of them must
match at least one of the fields. They do not have to match the same
field.
* Updated tests to confirm the above functionality.
Added more details to the `find` and `sort` commands.
